s are protected by a special status from the Byzantine Empire and are still recognized by the Hellenic State. The Holy Mountain is under the spiritual authority of the Ecumenical Patriarchate of Constantinople. This spiritual and artistic mecca is on the World Heritage List of UNESCO. \r\nThe duration of the cruise is three hours. The boat sails along the southwest coast of the peninsula and you can admire the eight monasteries and hermitages along the coastline. Overnight in the city of Thessaloniki.\r\n\r\n<span class="number">09</span> Ninth Day Departure\r\n\r\nAfter enjoying our last moments in Thessaloniki, we depart for the Thessaloniki Airport.\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="download-links">\r\n<a href="http://localhost/crossroad/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Religius-Historical-Greece.pdf" download class="download">download pdf</a>\r\n<a href="http://get.adobe.com/reader/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.adobe.com/images/shared/download_buttons/get_adobe_reader.gif"></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-6"><div class="map">[nwm_map id="1"]</div></div>\r\n', 'Religius & Historical Greece', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '319-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-01 01:58:58', '2015-12-01 01:58:58', '', 319, 'http://localhost/crossroad/319-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
